              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer509187388638705523">Wow, I really dug this Gide tale. Zany and witty, I think it would make a great screwball comedy movie, I hope someone makes it! Then there is this Avant-garde/Surrealist fascination with unmotivated murder, from the André Breton quip, <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17383628.Andr__Breton_Arbiter_of_Surrealism' title='André Breton Arbiter of Surrealism by Clifford Browder' rel='nofollow noopener'>André Breton: Arbiter of Surrealism</a> (&quot;“The simplest Surrealist act,” wrote André Breton, founder of Surrealism, “consists of dashing down into the street, pistol in hand and firing blindly, as fast as you can pull the trigger, into the crowd.”) to the Surrealist A</span>
  <span id="freeText509187388638705523" style="display:none">Wow, I really dug this Gide tale. Zany and witty, I think it would make a great screwball comedy movie, I hope someone makes it! Then there is this Avant-garde/Surrealist fascination with unmotivated murder, from the André Breton quip, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17383628.Andr__Breton_Arbiter_of_Surrealism" title="André Breton Arbiter of Surrealism by Clifford Browder" rel="nofollow noopener">André Breton: Arbiter of Surrealism</a> ("“The simplest Surrealist act,” wrote André Breton, founder of Surrealism, “consists of dashing down into the street, pistol in hand and firing blindly, as fast as you can pull the trigger, into the crowd.”) to the Surrealist Anti-Novel innovator Camus and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/49552.The_Stranger" title="The Stranger by Albert Camus" rel="nofollow noopener">The Stranger</a> ... all these random acts of violence and the dwelling on the psyche that leads to a random killing. It all seems motivated by a modernistic ennui and chilling when artfully done so...</span>
  <a data-text-id="509187388638705523" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

